en_948842_0	A sudden wildfire that broke out in the general area of Diyathalawa Railway Station was brought under control on Friday (31).
en_948842_1	The fire broke out due to prevailing spell of dry weather patterns that have enveloped the area with gushing winds from time to time.
en_948842_2	Troops managed to douse the wildfire within a couple of hours.
en_948842_3	21 troops including Officers serving the SF-C reacted immediately on the instructions of the Commander SF-C Major General Laksiri Waduge and brought the fire under control.
